It is illegal to import or sell alcohol without a licence. It is also illegal to drink alcohol in a public place, including at the Landing, the Public Square and the Western Harbour.
The main religion on Pitcairn is Seventh Day Adventism, and the Sabbath is observed on Saturday. All religions are welcome in the church.
In order to protect the islandâ€™s unique environment, the import of honey is forbidden, and the import of plant and animal products is strictly controlled; visitors wishing to import such items should contact the Pitcairns Island Office in Auckland for advice before travelling, and declare any such items on arrival to Pitcairn Island. Travellers with dogs should be aware of these restrictions and seek advice prior to travelling.
There is one grocery store on Pitcairn Island, which is open 3 times a week for 2 hours each time. Internet facilities are limited on Pitcairn although homestay guests will normally have access to local wifi facilities (possibly at additional cost).
Same sex marriage has been legal in the Pitcairn Islands since 2015.
